======
RULES
======

(=============== Main loop ====================)

[  ] -> [ HeroCell]
up   [ HeroCell | ] -> [|]
left [ HeroCell | ] -> [|]


[ stationary Background ] -> [ action Background ]
[ Solid ][ action Background ] -> [ Solid ][ Background ]
[ action Background ] -> status Thank you for opening the world.
[ HeroCell Tick:s20 ][ action Background ] -> [ HeroCell ][ action Background ]

[ action player Exit ] -> win




lock  [ > Player:direction:lock  ] -> [ > Player:>:lock ]
color  [ > AntiPlayer:direction:color  ] -> [ > AntiPlayer:>:color ]

[ HeroCell ][ > player ] -> [ action HeroCell KeyPress:> ][ player ]


[stationary HeroCell ] -> gosub RealTimeTick




[ Exit VictorySound no player ] -> [ Exit ]
late [ player Exit no VictorySound ] -> [ VictorySound player Exit ]
late [ player Exit ] -> status gg. Press X to continue
[ moving player Exit ] -> [ stationary player Exit ]




(================================================================================)
subroutine RealTimeTick


[ HeroCell no Tick:s20 ] -> [ HeroCell Tick:m19 ]
s20 [ stationary Tick:s20 ] -> [ action Tick:next20 ]


[ HeroCell Tick:even ] -> gosub ActivatePlayerMovement



( So the thing about all of this is that the mechanics of the game can trigger chain reactions and
sometimes even infinite loops)

(But if the reactions happen instantly, it looks like, bad)

(But I also don't want to always have a delay between cause and effect, because it can enable
a  lot of cheese)

(Throughought a whole month of tweaks I tried many ways to tackle this problem. I am very happy with
the current version)

( The first time the state of a color changes, the next open/close triggers inmediately.
But the consecutive triggers are delayed.
There is a 'cooldown' effect after forcing the first effect trigger, so that if triggers are happening
constantly, this effect will not happen again until things slow down for a while)

(Additionally, I made the distance between triggers not constant, that makes it sound like it is
doing music instead of just looping infinitely)


(Before maybe  running the locks logic, check if the state of goal cells has changed)
[ HeroCell ] -> gosub Goals 

(Run the Lock logic but only on certain occasions)

s20 [ HeroCell Tick:odd stationary LockTick:s20 ] -> [ HeroCell Tick:odd action LockTick:next20 ]
[ HeroCell Tick:odd no LockTick:s20 ] -> [ HeroCell Tick:odd LockTick:m0 ]

[ HeroCell Tick:odd GoalStateChanged no LockCooldown ] -> [ HeroCell Tick:odd GoalStateChanged LockCooldown ExecuteLockLogic LockTick:m0 ]

[ HeroCell Tick:odd LockCooldown LockTick:m19 ] -> [ HeroCell Tick:odd LockTick:m19 ]


[ HeroCell LockRate ] -> [ HeroCell LockRate ExecuteLockLogic ]


[ ExecuteLockLogic no LockRate  ] -> []

[ HeroCell Tick:odd ExecuteLockLogic ] -> [HeroCell Tick:odd] gosub Locks 



(Now the movement)
[ Moving:direction ] -> []
[ > player ] -> [ > player Moving:> ]
[ Error ] -> []
[ HeroCell ] -> gosub SpreadMovement

[ Moving:> Solid | Wall ] -> [ Error Solid | Wall ]

[ HeroCell ] -> gosub SpreadErrors


[ Moving:direction ] -> []
[ > player no Error ] -> [ stationary player Moving:> ]
[ HeroCell ] -> gosub SpreadMovement
[ Moving:> Solid ] -> [ > Solid ]


[ HeroCell ] ->  gosub Animations



(================================================================================)
subroutine ActivatePlayerMovement

[ no KeyPress:> ActiveMoving:> ] -> []
[ no KeyPress:> ReallyMoving:> ] -> []


[ HeroCell ReallyMoving:> stationary KeyPress:> ] -> [ HeroCell ReallyMoving:> action KeyPress:> ]

[ HeroCell ActiveMoving:> ] -> [ HeroCell ActiveMoving:> ReallyMoving:> ]

[ HeroCell stationary KeyPress:> no ActiveMoving:>] -> [ HeroCell action KeyPress:> ActiveMoving:> ExecuteLockLogic ReallyMoving:>]
([ HeroCell stationary KeyPress:> no ActiveMoving:>] -> [ HeroCell action KeyPress:> ActiveMoving:>  ])



[ HeroCell action KeyPress:> ][ stationary player ] -> [ HeroCell action KeyPress:>][ > player ]

[ KeyPress:> ] -> []





(================================================================================)
subroutine SpreadMovement


startloop
 [ Moving:> Solid | Pushable no Error ] -> [ Moving:> Solid | Moving:> Pushable]
 
 
 direction [ Moving:direction Sticky | Pushable no Error ] -> [ Moving:direction Sticky | Moving:direction Pushable ] SFX1
 direction [ Moving:direction Solid  | Sticky   no Error ] -> [ Moving:direction Solid  | Moving:direction Sticky   ] SFX1

endloop

subroutine SpreadErrors

startloop
 [ Moving:> | Error ] ->  [ Error Moving:> | Error ]
endloop

(==========================================================)
subroutine Goals 
(Evaluate All:color, if the state changed, HeroCell will be actioned)

[ HeroCell GoalStateChanged ] -> [ HeroCell ]

color [ Cross:color With:color no PresenceSFX:color ] -> [ Cross:color With:color PresenceSFX:color ]
color [ PresenceSFX:color no With:color ] -> []




(Evaluate All)
color [ HeroCell ] -> [ HeroCell All:color ]
color [ HeroCell All:color][ Cross:color no With:color ] -> [HeroCell][ Cross:color ]

color [ HeroCell PreviouslyAll:color no All:color ] -> [ HeroCell PreviouslyAll:color GoalStateChanged]
color [ HeroCell All:color no PreviouslyAll:color ] -> [ HeroCell All:color           GoalStateChanged]

[ PreviouslyAll:color ] -> []
color [ HeroCell All:color ] -> [ HeroCell PreviouslyAll:color All:color ]





(========================================================)
subroutine Locks

[ ExecuteOpen:antistate:color      ] -> []
[ ExecuteClose:antistate:color     ] -> []
[ AlmostClose:antistate:color     ] -> []


(Open)

color [ HeroCell All:color ][ Closed:color no Open:color ] -> [HeroCell All:color][ Closed:color ExecuteOpen:notanti:color ]
(Close)
color [ HeroCell no All:color ][ Open:color ] -> [ HeroCell ][ Open:color AlmostClose:notanti:color ]

(Anti-Open)

color [ HeroCell no All:color ][ AntiClosed:color no OpenAnti:color ] -> [ HeroCell ][ AntiClosed:color ExecuteOpen:anti:color ]
(Anti-Close)
color [ HeroCell All:color    ][ OpenAnti:color ] -> [ HeroCell All:color ][ OpenAnti:color AlmostClose:anti:color ]

(Make sure there are no solids in close)
antistate color [ AlmostClose:antistate:color no Solid ] -> [ ExecuteClose:antistate:color ]

color [ AlmostClose:notanti:color Open:color ]  -> [ action Open:color ]
color [ AlmostClose:anti:color OpenAnti:color ] -> [ action OpenAnti:color ]



(I used all those Execute: objects to simplify the rules, but it doesn't really seem
like it simplified them that much)

(Execute Open)

color other_color [ ExecuteOpen:notanti:color Block:other_color:color ] -> [ OpenBlock:other_color:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:notanti:color Wall:color     ] -> [ OpenWall:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:notanti:color Player:direction:color   ] -> [ OpenPlayer:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:notanti:color WildCard:color ] -> [ OpenWildCard:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:notanti:color Glue:color     ] -> [ OpenGlue:color ]

color other_color [ ExecuteOpen:anti:color AntiBlock:other_color:color ] -> [ OpenAntiBlock:other_color:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:anti:color AntiWall:color     ] -> [ OpenAntiWall:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:anti:color AntiPlayer:direction:color   ] -> [ OpenAntiPlayer:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:anti:color AntiWildCard:color ] -> [ OpenAntiWildCard:color ]
color [ ExecuteOpen:anti:color AntiGlue:color     ] -> [ OpenAntiGlue:color ]


(Execute Close)

color other_color [ ExecuteClose:notanti:color OpenBlock:other_color:color ] -> [ action Block:other_color:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:notanti:color OpenWall:color     ] -> [ action Wall:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:notanti:color OpenPlayer:color   ] -> [ action Player:right:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:notanti:color OpenWildCard:color ] -> [ action WildCard:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:notanti:color OpenGlue:color     ] -> [ action Glue:color ]

color other_color [ ExecuteClose:anti:color OpenAntiBlock:other_color:color ] -> [ action AntiBlock:other_color:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:anti:color OpenAntiWall:color     ] -> [ action AntiWall:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:anti:color OpenAntiPlayer:color   ] -> [ action AntiPlayer:right:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:anti:color OpenAntiWildCard:color ] -> [ action AntiWildCard:color ]
color [ ExecuteClose:anti:color OpenAntiGlue:color     ] -> [ action AntiGlue:color ]



(============================================)
subroutine Animations


color [ Cross:color With:color ] -> [ action Cross:color With:color ]
color  [ action Cross:color no CrossSprite:s4:color] -> [ action Cross:color CrossSprite:m0:color ]
s4 color  [ no Cross:color CrossSprite:s4:color] -> [ ]
s4 color  [ stationary Cross:color CrossSprite:s4:color] -> [ stationary Cross:color ]


s4 color [ stationary CrossSprite:s4:color  ] -> [ action CrossSprite:next4:color ]


[ HeroCell no Tick:m0 ][ action Open:color     ] -> [ HeroCell ][ stationary Open:color ]
[ HeroCell no Tick:m0 ][ action OpenAnti:color ] -> [ HeroCell ][ stationary OpenAnti:color ]

